Preheat your #oven{} to 220 C. Halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1} into thin half moons. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve the strips widthways. Trim the @courgette{1} then slice into rounds about 1⁄2cm thick. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain the @mozzarella{1}, tear it roughly and then pop on a sheet of #kitchen paper{} (so it soaks up the moisture).

Put the @pizza base{1} onto a large #baking tray{}. In a #small bowl{}, stir the garlic into the @tomato puree{30%g}. Spread evenly onto the pizza base using the back of a #spoon{}. Remember to leave space for the crust!

Place the veggies and mozzarella over the tomato purée, ensuring there is an even covering of veggies and mozzarella. Finally, scatter over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Season with a good grind of @pepper{} and drizzle with a little @olive oil{}.

Pop the pizza onto the top shelf of your oven to cook until the base is golden around the edges and the cheese is melted and bubbly, about ~{12-15%minutes}.

While the pizza cooks, pop the @wild rocket{40%g} in a #mixing bowl{} and toss with the @olive oil{for the dressing} and a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss gently to coat the leaves.

Serve the pizza with a handful of rocket in the centre of each and any remaining leaves on the side. Enjoy!

> This deliciously simple, chef-curated veggie pizza with courgette, red pepper and red onion is perfect for pizza night!

